<main>
  <h1 class="portfolio-header">Projects</h1>
  <div class="text-projects">
    <h2 style="text-decoration: underline">Portfolio Website</h2>
    <p >The creation of this website is powered by Ruby on Rails. The main goal was to showcase the basic operations of CRUD and who I am as a person. The side goal was to learn more about the MVC design pattern hands on.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="slider-container" id="slider1">
    <div class="slider">
      <div class="slide">
        <a href="<%= image_path 'routes.png' %>" data-lightbox="gallery" data-title="Rails Routes">
          <%= image_tag "routes.png", alt: "about page html" %>
        </a>
        <p style="font-style: italic; font-size: 4mm;">Click to image enlarge</p>
        <p>Rails router, contact form does all the CRUD </p>
        <p>Router sends user to appropriate pages by routing them to the page controller</p>
      </div>
      <div class="slide">
        <a href="<%= image_path 'contact_form_controller.png' %>" data-lightbox="gallery" data-title="Contact Form Controller">
          <%= image_tag "contact_form_controller.png", alt: "contact form controller" %>
        </a>
        <p style="font-style: italic; font-size: 4mm;">Click image to enlarge</p>
        <p>Description </p>
      </div>
      <div class="slide">
        <a href="<%= image_path 'application_html_view.png' %>" data-lightbox="gallery" data-title="Application View ">
          <%= image_tag "application_html_view.png", alt: "application view page" %>
        </a>
        <p style="font-style: italic; font-size: 4mm;">Click image to enlarge</p>
        <p>Description </p>
      </div>
      <div class="slide">
        <a href="<%= image_path 'slider_javascript.png' %>" data-lightbox="gallery" data-title="Slider Javascript">
          <%= image_tag "slider_javascript.png", alt: "slider js" %>
        </a>
        <p style="font-style: italic; font-size: 4mm;">Click image to enlarge</p>
        <p>My javascript for slider</p>
      </div>
      <div class="slide">
        <a href="<%= image_path 'pages_css.png' %>" data-lightbox="gallery" data-title="pages">
          <%= image_tag "pages_css.png", alt: "page html" %>
        </a>
        <p style="font-style: italic; font-size: 4mm;">Click image to enlarge</p>
        <p>Description </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="slider-buttons">
    <button class="slider-btn" onclick="prevSlide(0)">❮ Prev</button>
    <button class="slider-btn" onclick="nextSlide(0)">Next ❯</button>
  </div>

  <div class="text-projects">
    <h2 style="text-decoration: underline"> ArborPro LLC Tree Service Website</h2>
    <p >A friend of mine had issues with his free business website on Google being basic. So, I volunteered to help him create his own website by using WordPress and Siteground to host it. I looked at his competitor's websites and pulled inspiration from their designs.</p>
    <a href="https://www.arborprocda.com/services/" class="button">View Website</a>
  </div>

  <div class="slider-container"  id="slider2">
    <div class="slider">
      <div class="slide">
        <a href="<%= image_path 'landing-page.png' %>" data-lightbox="gallery2" data-title="ArborPro Home Page">
          <%= image_tag "landing-page.png"%>
        </a>
        <p style="font-style: italic; font-size: 4mm;">Click image to enlarge</p>
        <p>Description</p>
      </div>
      <div class="slide">
        <a href="<%= image_path 'star-animation.png' %>" data-lightbox="gallery2" data-title="Star Animation">
          <%= image_tag "star-animation.png" %>
        </a>
        <p style="font-style: italic; font-size: 4mm;">Click image to enlarge</p>
        <p>Description 2</p>
      </div>
      <div class="slide">
        <a href="<%= image_path 'plugin.png' %>" data-lightbox="gallery2" data-title="Plugin Usage">
          <%= image_tag "plugin.png" %>
          <p style="font-style: italic; font-size: 4mm;">Click image to enlarge</p>
        </a>
        <p>Description 3</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
  <div class="slider-buttons">
    <button class="slider-btn" onclick="prevSlide(1)">❮ Prev</button>
    <button class="slider-btn" onclick="nextSlide(1)">Next ❯</button>
  </div>
</main>

<%= javascript_include_tag "slider", "data-turbo-track": "reload" %>
<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/lightbox2/2.11.3/js/lightbox.min.js"></script>
<script>
    lightbox.option({
        'positionFromTop': 125
    })
</script>